<task id="053" project="email-communication-solution-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>Audit and migrate any other `SendEmailDialog` consumers beyond FilePreview</title>
    <phase>Wave 3 — SendEmailDialog + FilePreview</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>2</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>050, 052</dependencies>
    <blocks>054</blocks>
    <tags>refactoring, audit, react, frontend</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Audit-then-migrate task; rigor scales with what the audit finds. If the audit surfaces only FilePreviewDialog (already handled by 051), this is a no-op verification. If it surfaces other consumers, each migration mirrors task 051 patterns — well-trodden territory. No new architectural decisions.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Sequential gate before Wave 3 build/deploy (054). Audit results must be settled before deploy to avoid shipping unmigrated consumers. Depends on task 052 (interface rename) being landed so audit can leverage TypeScript compiler errors as a discovery signal.</parallel-reason>
    <fr-refs>FR-14</fr-refs>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Perform a complete grep + TypeScript-compiler-error audit of `src/` to surface every consumer of the `SendEmailDialog` component beyond `LegalWorkspace/FilePreview/FilePreviewDialog.tsx`. Migrate each surfaced consumer inline using the canonical wrapper pattern established by task 051.

    Audit sources:
    1. `grep -rn 'SendEmailDialog' src/` — surfaces import statements + JSX usages
    2. `grep -rn 'ISendEmailDialogProps' src/` — surfaces type-level consumers
    3. `grep -rn 'onSend.*SendEmailDialog\|<SendEmailDialog' src/ -A 5` — surfaces legacy-callback usages
    4. After tasks 050+052 land: `npm run build` across all consuming packages will surface TypeScript compilation errors for any consumer still passing `onSend` — these are auto-discovery signals

    Document the audit findings in the PR description: for each surfaced consumer, list path + current usage shape + migration approach (or "already canonical / N/A").

    Expected outcome based on pre-flight: the only known consumer is `FilePreviewDialog.tsx` (handled by task 051). Pre-R3 the engine + wrappers did not exist, so direct `SendEmailDialog` imports were possible only from the legacy component. Audit MAY surface ZERO other consumers — that is an acceptable outcome (document "no other consumers found" in PR description and proceed).

    If a consumer IS found beyond FilePreview, migrate it using task 051's pattern:
    - Remove inline `fetch` to `/api/communications/send` (if present)
    - Replace legacy `onSend` callback with `onSent` / `onError`
    - Import `SendEmailDialog` from `@spaarke/ui-components`
    - Use canonical props
    - Build + lint clean
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Frontend developer authoritative on consumer-impact audits across the Spaarke repository. Comfortable with grep-based discovery, TypeScript compiler errors as an audit signal, and applying mechanical migration patterns.
  </role>

  <goal>
    A complete, audited list of every `SendEmailDialog` consumer in `src/` is produced. Every non-FilePreview consumer (if any) is migrated to the canonical wrapper. Zero remaining usages of the legacy `onSend` callback. Zero inline `fetch.*communications/send` in any consumer of `SendEmailDialog`. All affected packages build clean. PR description lists every surfaced consumer + migration status.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Task 050 produced an initial consumer audit list (recorded in `current-task.md`). THIS task takes that list, broadens it with additional grep patterns and TypeScript compiler errors (after task 052 landed the interface change), and migrates whatever the audit finds.

      Empirical state from pre-flight: pre-R3 the canonical wrapper did not exist; the only `SendEmailDialog` symbol in the repo was the legacy `Spaarke.UI.Components/.../SendEmailDialog/SendEmailDialog.tsx` component. The only known LegalWorkspace consumer is `FilePreviewDialog.tsx`. There MAY be additional consumers — for example:
      - Other LegalWorkspace components (CreateMatter, Project, etc. — though these mostly use `SendEmailStep` not `SendEmailDialog`)
      - PCF controls that bundle `@spaarke/ui-components`
      - Code Pages that mount the dialog
      - Other solutions (`SummarizeFilesWizard`, etc. — though Summarize uses `SendEmailStep` per Wave 4)

      The audit is mechanical; the migrations (if any) reuse task 051's pattern verbatim.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/ (entire tree — grep audit target)</file>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/current-task.md (initial audit list from task 050)</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SendEmailDialog/SendEmailDialog.tsx (canonical wrapper / re-export)</file>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/FilePreview/FilePreviewDialog.tsx (handled by 051 — skip)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec FR-14">Post-audit: zero consumers using legacy `onSend` callback; zero consumers with inline `fetch` to `/api/communications/send` via `SendEmailDialog` surfaces.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-033">Every migrated consumer uses the canonical wrapper from `@spaarke/ui-components` (NOT a fork, NOT a re-implementation).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-019">Migrated `onError` handlers use typed `SendCommunicationError`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">PR description MUST list every surfaced consumer + migration status (migrated / already canonical / no consumers found).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Do NOT touch `.claude/` paths from this task.</constraint>
    <constraint source="repo">All affected packages MUST build clean after migrations.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/plan.md</file>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/tasks/051-filepreviewdialog-migration.poml</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-033-communication-architecture.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-019-problemdetails-error-responses.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/api/send-email-integration.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Consumer migration template" location="projects/email-communication-solution-r3/tasks/051-filepreviewdialog-migration.poml">
        Task 051's step-by-step migration of FilePreviewDialog IS the template. For every non-FilePreview consumer found by the audit, apply this pattern.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Load the initial consumer audit list from `current-task.md` (produced by task 050).</step>
    <step order="2">Broaden the audit. Run grep across `src/`:
      <code>
      grep -rn 'SendEmailDialog' src/
      grep -rn 'ISendEmailDialogProps' src/
      grep -rn 'from .*ui-components.*SendEmailDialog\|from .*ui-components.*ISendEmailDialogProps' src/
      </code>
      Compile a deduplicated consumer list.
    </step>
    <step order="3">After task 052 landed the interface change, run `npm run build` across consumer packages — LegalWorkspace, any PCFs bundling `@spaarke/ui-components`, code-pages. Any TypeScript compilation error referencing `onSend` is a consumer that needs migration. Add those files to the audit list.</step>
    <step order="4">For each consumer in the audit list, classify: (a) already FilePreviewDialog (handled by 051 — skip), (b) already on canonical contract (no change needed — verify and document), (c) needs migration (apply task 051 pattern).</step>
    <step order="5">For consumers in category (c), apply task 051's migration pattern: import canonical wrapper, remove inline fetch (if any), replace `onSend` with `onSent`/`onError`, ensure attachments / associations / initial values are passed through. ONE consumer at a time; small atomic edits.</step>
    <step order="6">Run `npm run build` + `npm run lint` across every affected package after each migration. Verify clean.</step>
    <step order="7">Grep verify: zero `onSend.*SendEmailDialog` usages remain in `src/`. Zero `fetch.*communications/send` in any file consuming `SendEmailDialog`.</step>
    <step order="8">Write the audit summary to `notes/wave-3-sendemaildialog-consumer-audit.md` (project-internal, not `.claude/`). Include: full consumer list, classification, migration status.</step>
    <step order="9">Update `projects/email-communication-solution-r3/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 053 ✅ completed.</step>
    <step order="10">Update `projects/email-communication-solution-r3/current-task.md` per task-execute protocol: status → completed, advance to next pending task (054).</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="grep">Audit consumers across `src/`</tool>
    <tool name="bash">Run `npm run build` to surface TypeScript errors as audit signals</tool>
    <tool name="read">Inspect each surfaced consumer's current usage</tool>
    <tool name="edit">Apply task 051's migration pattern to non-FilePreview consumers</tool>
    <tool name="write">Create `notes/wave-3-sendemaildialog-consumer-audit.md` audit report</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="notes">projects/email-communication-solution-r3/notes/wave-3-sendemaildialog-consumer-audit.md (NEW — audit summary)</output>
    <output type="file">Any `*.tsx` files migrated (zero or more — depends on audit findings)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Audit list of `SendEmailDialog` consumers produced and committed to `notes/wave-3-sendemaildialog-consumer-audit.md`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Every non-FilePreview consumer (if any) is either migrated to canonical contract OR documented as already canonical.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Zero `onSend.*SendEmailDialog` patterns remaining in `src/` (grep verified).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Zero `fetch.*communications/send` patterns in any file consuming `SendEmailDialog` (grep verified).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">All affected packages build clean after migrations.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">PR description lists every surfaced consumer + migration status.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`TASK-INDEX.md` marks task 053 ✅ completed.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Expected outcome: the audit likely finds zero non-FilePreview consumers, in which case this task is a 30-minute verification + audit-report write-up. Empirical pre-flight scan did not surface other consumers, BUT a thorough audit is still required per spec FR-14 ("Audit for any other `SendEmailDialog` consumers and migrate inline").

    If the audit surfaces a complex consumer (e.g., one that wraps `SendEmailDialog` in a HOC or layered abstraction), document the discovery and decide: (a) inline migration if the wrapping is thin, or (b) escalate to project owner if the wrapping suggests the consumer should be re-architected. Default to (a) when possible.

    Do NOT delete the legacy `SendEmailDialog/` directory in this task. Task 050 may have already collapsed it to a re-export; do not touch beyond what 050 produced.

    Notes file location: per CLAUDE.md §3 (Sub-Agent Write Boundary), `.claude/` paths are off-limits to sub-agents. The audit report lives in `projects/email-communication-solution-r3/notes/` — project-internal, accessible to sub-agents and main session.
  </notes>

  <execution>
    <skill>.claude/skills/task-execute/SKILL.md</skill>
    <protocol>
      Load all `<knowledge><files>` before starting. Apply STANDARD rigor per `<rigor-hint>`. Quality gates at Step 9.5 (adr-check + code-review) SKIPPED for STANDARD rigor.
